sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as API Client
    participant Gateway as Kubeflow Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Proxy as model-registry proxy<br/>8080/TCP HTTP<br/>mTLS (Istio)
    participant DB as MySQL/PostgreSQL<br/>3306/5432 TCP<br/>TLS 1.2+
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Controller as controller-manager<br/>8081/TCP HTTP
    participant StorageInit as KServe Storage<br/>Initializer

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 1: REST API Client -> Model Registry

    Client->>Gateway: GET/POST /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/*<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS
    Gateway->>Proxy: Forward via VirtualService<br/>HTTP/8080, mTLS (Istio)<br/>AuthorizationPolicy: ALLOW
    Proxy->>DB: Query/Insert metadata<br/>3306/5432 TCP<br/>TLS 1.2+ (optional)<br/>Auth: username/password
    DB-->>Proxy: Result set
    Proxy-->>Gateway: JSON Response
    Gateway-->>Client: HTTPS Response

    Note over K8sAPI,Controller: Flow 2: InferenceService Controller Reconciliation

    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch InferenceService CR<br/>ServiceAccount token
    Controller->>Proxy: Sync metadata<br/>HTTP/8080<br/>plaintext/TLS (configurable)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (optional)
    Proxy-->>Controller: Metadata response
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update ISVC labels/finalizers<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token

    Note over StorageInit,Proxy: Flow 3: KServe Model Loading via Storage Initializer

    StorageInit->>Proxy: Resolve model-registry:// URI<br/>HTTP/8080, mTLS (Istio)
    Proxy-->>StorageInit: Model artifact location
    StorageInit->>StorageInit: Download model from<br/>resolved artifact location
